metadata.label: Title
metadata.value: Pro custodienta humilitate et cognitione humanae fragilitatis

metadata.label: Content
value: Part 1 contains: (ff. 1r-73r) Sermons, meditations and prayers. - Empty: f. 1*r-v, 68*r-68**v, 73v-73*v.
Part 2 contains: (ff. 74r-158v) Soliloquia animae ad Deum / Pseudo-Augustine of Hippo. Translation in Dutch.
Part 3 contains: (ff. 159r-174v) Prayers and devotional exercises.
Part 4 contains: (ff. 175r-185v) Hours of the Virgin. - (ff. 186r-205v) Life of the Virgin Mary. - Empty: f. 206v.
Part 5 contains: (ff. 207r-209v) Prayers. - Empty: ff. 209v-209*v, 209**r-v (former back pastedown).
Maculature. Flyleaves (ff. 1, 210) contain text from: Dietsche Catoen. Fragment.

metadata.label: Note
value: Decoration: Unfinished. With space reserved for initials.

Binding: Medieval binding, contemporary (original). - Medieval binding, contemporary (original). - Leather (brown, blind-tooled) over wooden boards. Decorated with panel stamp on both sides (Madonna with child sitting on crescent moon); text: "Mulier

Textual: Devotional miscellany. - (ff. 1r-73v) Contains among others a Dutch translation of Pro custodienta humilitate et cognitione humanae fragilitatis. - (ff 74r-158v) Dutch translation. - (flyleaves) Dutch adaptation of the Disticha Catonis.
Also described by Handschriftencensus and MMDC.
